AUSTRALIAN OPEN
January 25, 2015
Andreas Seppi
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   


  N. KYRGIOS/A. Seppi  5-7, 4-6, 6-3, 7-6, 8-6  An interview with:  ANDREAS SEPPI   THE MODERATOR: Questions, please.   Q.  After the fourth set you missed a match point.  Beginning of the fifth set you seemed disappointed and went down quickly a break.  How much did that affect you missing the match point?  ANDREAS SEPPI: Yeah, of course, I was a little bit down.  Also the energy after the fourth set, you know, was a little bit down.  But, yeah, I think in the middle of the fifth set then we played again some good tennis.  He served well in important moments.  That was the key.  That's why he won, I think.   Q.  Was there anything that changed in the third set when he started to get on top?  ANDREAS SEPPI: No, I think I just played a couple bad games at the beginning of the third set.  I missed three easy forehands for the break for him.  And, yeah, maybe he played a little bit more relaxed after that.  Yeah, I think maybe if I could stay even in the third set it's a little bit already change, you know.  
 

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT